g.text: A Java Library that helps read record from a Kinesis Data Stream with distributed applications sharing the read workload.
* Each shard is to be read by only one KCL instance, i.e; 4 shards = 4 KCL instances, 6 shards = 6 KCL instances.
- Data comes into Kinesis (like website clicks or logs).
- KCL application reads that data from each shard.
- KCL keeps track of which records have been processed using DynamoDB (this is called checkpointing).
- If a worker stops or fails, KCL automatically transfers its work to another worker.
* Records are read in order at the shard level.
